  "texts": [
    "Methodology Overview of the ApproachThe proposed approach involves augmenting the Llama model with a reverse proxy-style Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) mechanism to enhance factual accuracy.",
    "The concept of reverse proxy-style RAG centers around integrating an intermediary layer between the LLM and the external data sources.",
    "This intermediary layer functions as a reverse proxy, intercepting and processing queries from the LLM, retrieving relevant information from external databases, and then feeding the enriched data back to the LLM for generating more accurate and contextually appropriate responses.",
    "By employing this approach, the system dynamically incorporates real-time information into the generative process, thereby mitigating the limitations of static training data and improving the overall factual accuracy of the model's outputs.The core idea behind reverse proxy-style RAG is to leverage the strengths of both retrieval-based and generation-based models.",
    "The retrieval component, acting as a reverse proxy, ensures that the most relevant and up-to-date information is accessed and provided to the LLM."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}